# o9ds authoring patterns (single reference)

Use these **instead of inventing** new markup for the same jobs. Extend this rule when a new pattern becomes standard.

## Layout & doc chrome

Follow **`.cursor/rules/o9ds-layout-components.mdc`** — reuse `PageWithToc`, `PageHeader`, `WhiteBgCard`, `GrayBgCard`, `DocTable`, `DocTabs`, `CodeBlock`, `ExpandableDocImage`, `ComponentOverviewCard`, `SectionOverviewPage`, etc.

## o9con icons (React)

- **Pattern:** `<span className="o9con {icon.class} o9ds-icon-{size}" aria-hidden />` (add `dark:text-white` or inline `color` when the page needs theme contrast).
- **Icon list / class names:** `src/tokens/o9conIcons.js` (regenerate from CSS via `npm run generate:o9con-icons` after font updates).
- **Reference UI:** `src/pages/foundation/Icons.jsx` (gallery + snippets).
- **Example in content:** `src/pages/Overview.jsx` (`o9con-speaker`).

## Semantic colors & tokens

- **JS token tables / semantics:** `src/tokens/semanticColorTokens.js`, `globalColorTokens.js`, `brandColors.js`.
- **How we document color on the site:** `src/pages/foundation/Colors.jsx` (swatches, tables, copy patterns).
- **Global CSS variables / theme:** `src/index.css` (prefer existing `text-o9ds-*` / semantic CSS vars already used on doc pages).

## Inline code vs blocks

- **Multi-line or copyable snippets:** `CodeBlock` from `src/LayoutComponents/CodeBlock.jsx`.
- **Usage/API docs with structured sections:** `DocSection` helpers from `src/LayoutComponents/DocSection.jsx` — use **`DocCode`** for inline identifiers (`prop` names, `aria-*`, class names), **`DocStrong`**, **`DocParagraph`**, etc. Reference: `src/pages/usage/Accessibility.jsx`, component pages using `DocSection`.
- **Plain inline code in prose:** existing pages use `<code className="..." data-o9ds-inline-code>` where needed — match neighboring paragraphs on the same file.

## Component doc pages (`/components/...`)

Follow **`.cursor/rules/o9ds-component-docs.mdc`** — four tabs only; **reference implementation:** `src/pages/components/buttons-actions/Button.jsx`.

## When you add a new standard pattern

1. Implement it once in a **canonical file** (prefer an existing reference page).
2. Add **one bullet** to this rule pointing to that file.
3. Optionally add a line under **Folder structure** in `README.md` if it is a new top-level doc type.
